p0126 = "O wonder, newer than all wonders! For a Virgin who did not know man conceived in the womb him who controls all things, yet he was not circumscribed."
p0127 = "When he reaches the doors of the Church for the last time, the Bishop exclaims with a loud voice:"
p0128 = "Blessed are you, Christ our God, to the ages of ages. Amen."
p0129 = "Then the following Troparion is sung in Tone 3."
p0130 = "Christ God, who founded your Church on the rock of the faith, direct our entreaties in it and accept a people that cries out to you, \u2018Save us, our God!\u2019"
p0131 = "While the above Troparion is being chanted, the Bishop places the holy Relics on the table and, when the Troparion is finished, the Deacon exclaims:"
